		"preferredVictoryType": "Scientific",

		"startIntroPart1": "Hail, Librarian, keeper of the Archive! When the Great Catastrophe reduced civilization to ash and silence, it was your predecessors who risked everything to save what remained of human knowledge. From burning libraries and crumbling server rooms, they rescued hard drives, manuscripts, and blueprints, carrying them through the poisoned wastes to a fortified bunker deep beneath the old university district. There, surrounded by the last flickering generators, The Archive was born - a faction dedicated to preserving every scrap of science, history, and technology so that humanity might one day rebuild from more than rubble.",
		"startIntroPart2": "Librarian, the shelves groan with the weight of a dead world's wisdom, and your scholars labor day and night to decode what was saved. But knowledge without action is merely memory. Will you take what The Archive has preserved and forge it into a new civilization? The wasteland awaits a mind sharp enough to rebuild. Will EmpireForge rise under the light of rediscovered knowledge?",

        "declaringWar": "We have studied your weaknesses in our records, and the data is conclusive - you must be eliminated. Knowledge is the ultimate weapon, and we wield it now!",
		"attacked": "You dare assault the keepers of humanity's legacy? Every book you burn, every lab you destroy, is a crime against the future!",
		"defeated": "The Archive falls... but knowledge cannot be killed. Somewhere, a copy survives. It always does.",
		"denounced": "Our records show exactly what you are - a threat to the recovery of civilization itself.",
		"introduction": "I am the Librarian, voice of The Archive. We have preserved the knowledge of the old world. Are you here to learn, or to burn?",

		"neutralHello": "Speak. Knowledge waits for no one.",
		"hateHello": "What does an illiterate scavenger want with The Archive?",

		"tradeRequest": "We have blueprints, formulas, and medical texts you desperately need. This exchange benefits us both - consider it carefully.",

		"outerColor": [60,70,100],
		"innerColor": [180,200,230],
		"uniqueName": "Ingenuity",
