        "startIntroPart1": "Salute the Engineer, master of The Factory! When the Great Catastrophe silenced the machines and darkened the forges, a crew of industrial workers and mechanics refused to let the engines die. In a massive manufacturing complex on the outskirts of a ruined megacity, they kept the turbines spinning and the assembly lines moving. Scavenging raw materials from the wreckage, The Factory became the only faction capable of mass-producing tools, weapons, and vehicles. Their smokestacks rise above the wasteland like iron monuments to human defiance, and the rhythmic pounding of their hammers can be heard for miles.",
        "startIntroPart2": "Engineer, your furnaces burn hot and your workers are tireless. But production without purpose is mere noise. Will you direct The Factory's output toward rebuilding civilization itself? The wasteland needs machines, and machines need a master. Will EmpireForge be built on the anvil of industry?",

