        "startIntroPart1": "Ahoy, Captain, admiral of The Fleet! When the Great Catastrophe drowned coastal cities and poisoned the inland waters, those who knew the sea found salvation on the waves. The Captain gathered shipwrights, sailors, and fishermen aboard a flotilla of salvaged vessels - tankers, freighters, and fishing boats lashed together into floating strongholds. The Fleet controls the coasts, the shipping lanes, and the precious trade routes that connect scattered survivor settlements. Where others see a hostile ocean, The Fleet sees highways, harbors, and opportunity stretching to every horizon.",
