        "startIntroPart1": "Behold the Artist, visionary of The Movement! When the Great Catastrophe silenced the music and burned the galleries, most survivors forgot what it meant to be human. But not The Movement. From the ruins of theaters and museums, the Artist gathered painters, poets, musicians, and dreamers who believed that civilization without culture is merely organized survival. They paint murals on bunker walls, perform plays by firelight, and preserve the songs and stories that remind humanity why it is worth saving at all. The Movement proves that even in the darkest wasteland, beauty endures.",
